WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.836
CLAIRE: Previously,
on The Good Doctor...

00:02.870 --> 00:05.239
Can we just hold each other
for a little bit?

00:08.642 --> 00:09.943
Deal with your crap

00:09.977 --> 00:11.812
before this is
who you really become.

00:14.515 --> 00:17.151
I'm sorry for
making you meet me
after hours like this.

00:17.185 --> 00:18.652
I'm always available
for my patients.

00:18.686 --> 00:20.054
Come on in.

00:20.088 --> 00:22.056
Your dad's been diagnosed
with pancreatic cancer.

00:22.090 --> 00:24.125
You're not like
other people.

00:24.158 --> 00:27.361
You're like
a spoiled, little baby.

00:27.395 --> 00:28.496
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

00:30.064 --> 00:31.932
(BREATHING NORMALIZES)

00:31.965 --> 00:33.867
**

00:36.504 --> 00:38.906
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

00:50.651 --> 00:52.386
Shaun?

00:52.420 --> 00:54.222
You okay?

00:54.255 --> 00:57.325
We have to be
at the airport
at 7:00 a.m.

00:57.358 --> 00:59.993
I think when you're
taking the first flight
out of Casper,

01:00.027 --> 01:01.662
you don't need to be there
90 minutes early.

01:01.695 --> 01:02.996
Mm.

01:04.465 --> 01:05.866
Or maybe you do.

01:09.370 --> 01:11.239
(SIGHS)

01:11.272 --> 01:13.441
You want to talk
about last night?

01:15.409 --> 01:16.744
I think we should.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.849
Why?

01:21.882 --> 01:24.818
Because you were in
a pretty bad place,

01:24.852 --> 01:26.687
which is
totally understanda...

01:26.720 --> 01:28.522
I feel better now.

01:28.556 --> 01:30.424
Thank you.

01:30.458 --> 01:32.726
**

01:35.729 --> 01:37.631
I'm glad
I could help you.

01:39.567 --> 01:42.035
But I also think

01:42.069 --> 01:44.538
we shouldn't tell anyone
I stayed here all night.

01:44.572 --> 01:45.906
People might
get the wrong idea.

01:47.608 --> 01:48.676
Okay.

02:13.334 --> 02:14.535
We slept together.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.615
Did you use protection?

02:27.648 --> 02:31.819
N-No.
We did not have sex.
We just slept.

02:33.187 --> 02:34.188
Together.

02:35.088 --> 02:36.156
Held each other.

02:36.190 --> 02:37.725
I was upset,
and Lea comforted me.

02:41.795 --> 02:45.699
Lying in bed with her,

02:45.733 --> 02:47.167
it felt...

02:49.837 --> 02:51.972
Different than it does
with Carly.

02:52.940 --> 02:55.543
Well, maybe that's why
you invited Lea

02:55.576 --> 02:57.678
instead of Carly
in the first place?

02:57.711 --> 02:59.247
Mm.

02:59.280 --> 03:00.914
Lea and I
are just friends.

03:00.948 --> 03:02.750
Yeah, she's made that
very clear.

03:04.151 --> 03:05.986
Sometimes you learn
more about someone

03:06.019 --> 03:09.189
by what they do
than what they say.

03:09.223 --> 03:10.824
Of course,
who the hell knows
what she wants.

03:10.858 --> 03:12.493
But more importantly,
what do you want?

03:16.297 --> 03:17.298
I don't know.

03:19.500 --> 03:20.968
Well, you better
figure it out soon.

03:22.169 --> 03:26.039
Sex or no sex,
the wheels are in motion.

03:26.073 --> 03:28.676
And someone's about
to get run over.

03:30.844 --> 03:32.212
They had Mallomars.

03:32.246 --> 03:33.481
Let's roll.

03:33.514 --> 03:36.183
**

03:37.685 --> 03:39.753
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:51.865 --> 03:53.301
(P.A. SYSTEM BEEPS)

03:53.334 --> 03:55.035
WOMAN ON P.A.:
Respiratory tech to 3 East.

03:55.068 --> 03:56.537
Respiratory tech to 3 East.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.439
Shaun,
y-you're back already?

03:58.472 --> 04:01.008
Why wouldn't I be?
I like being here.

04:01.041 --> 04:02.175
Shaun.

04:04.378 --> 04:06.714
I'm really sorry
to hear about your father.

04:06.747 --> 04:07.781
How are you doing?

04:07.815 --> 04:08.982
He died.

04:09.016 --> 04:11.552
And the seat was
very uncomfortable
on the flight,

04:11.585 --> 04:12.786
so I couldn't sleep.

04:12.820 --> 04:14.788
And they only had
the salty peanuts

04:14.822 --> 04:16.357
and not the pretzels
I like.

04:18.191 --> 04:19.827
Yeah. Life sucks.

04:20.961 --> 04:22.696
We need a doctor!

04:22.730 --> 04:24.365
**

04:25.966 --> 04:28.201
(BREATHING HEAVILY)
We were mountain biking.

04:28.235 --> 04:30.070
She fell down
a rocky slide.

04:30.103 --> 04:31.439
Her leg...

04:34.308 --> 04:36.644
We'll need an X-ray
and an MRI.

04:36.677 --> 04:37.911
Let's also get you
something stronger

04:37.945 --> 04:39.813
than this ice pack
for the pain.
N-No.

04:39.847 --> 04:42.383
Uh, they gave me Vicodin when
I had my wisdom teeth pulled.

04:42.416 --> 04:43.584
I was sick for two days.

04:43.617 --> 04:45.252
We have
other painkillers...

04:45.285 --> 04:46.987
Really, I'm fine.

04:47.020 --> 04:49.256
Look, I made it through
childbirth without drugs.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.558
I can make it
through this.

04:50.591 --> 04:52.660
That hurts
less than childbirth?

04:52.693 --> 04:54.462
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

05:00.000 --> 05:01.068
CLAIRE:
Tender and bloated.

05:01.101 --> 05:03.637
We should
get you admitted,
get an X-ray.

05:03.671 --> 05:05.806
That's all right.
All I need are laxatives.

05:05.839 --> 05:07.941
Intestinal blockage could be
fatal if we don't treat it.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.379
Please.

05:11.412 --> 05:13.847
I'm unemployed, and I don't
have insurance right now.

05:17.250 --> 05:18.552
How about this...

05:18.586 --> 05:22.089
We skip the X-ray,
give you the meds.

05:22.122 --> 05:24.658
But in exchange,
you agree to stay here

05:24.692 --> 05:26.026
till you've had
a bowel movement,

05:26.059 --> 05:27.194
and we have
peace of mind.

05:29.897 --> 05:30.898
Deal.

05:38.338 --> 05:39.473
Shaun, you're back.

05:39.507 --> 05:41.975
Hello, Carly.
It's good to see you.
I missed you.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.577
Morgan and I
have a patient

05:43.611 --> 05:45.813
with a comminuted
leg fracture.

05:45.846 --> 05:48.882
We need a rush on a C.B.C.
and coagulation panel.

05:50.651 --> 05:52.185
Shaun, I'm sorry
about your Dad.

05:53.821 --> 05:56.490
Why didn't you return
any of my calls or texts?

05:57.357 --> 05:59.727
I was very busy.

06:01.161 --> 06:02.863
You had time to text me.

06:04.498 --> 06:05.866
I wasn't sure
what to say.

06:07.401 --> 06:11.304
Shaun, I know that you
don't always understand
people's feelings.

06:13.006 --> 06:14.542
But a part of you
had to understand

06:14.575 --> 06:16.176
that ignoring me
would be hurtful.

06:19.413 --> 06:21.281
I'm not sure
what to say now.

06:21.314 --> 06:23.484
(SIGHS)

06:23.517 --> 06:25.786
**

06:27.588 --> 06:29.757
My patient
is getting an MRI.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.959
I need to get back
to them.

06:35.763 --> 06:37.364
Are you going to
take the samples?

06:49.777 --> 06:51.278
(DOOR OPENS)

06:52.112 --> 06:53.113
Hey.

06:55.516 --> 06:56.517
PTSD.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.553
It's an interesting
topic.

06:59.587 --> 07:02.255
Just organizing some notes
for a potential case report.

07:02.289 --> 07:03.891
Nice. Look forward
to reading it.

07:07.761 --> 07:09.530
I started
seeing a therapist.

07:13.066 --> 07:14.067
Good.

07:15.569 --> 07:16.770
I hope you find it
helpful.

07:16.804 --> 07:17.805
Mm.

07:19.540 --> 07:22.676
She thinks I, uh...
I might have PTSD.

07:22.710 --> 07:24.978
Sounds a bit excessive.

07:25.012 --> 07:26.780
You've definitely dealt with
some childhood trauma.

07:28.415 --> 07:29.449
You think she's right?

07:29.483 --> 07:31.985
I think doctors make
the worst patients.

07:32.019 --> 07:33.320
Mm.

07:33.353 --> 07:36.089
The best patients
are the ones who ask
a lot of questions.

07:36.123 --> 07:38.058
And keep an open mind.

07:38.091 --> 07:39.627
**

07:43.196 --> 07:44.765
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

07:45.799 --> 07:47.000
(GRUNTS)

07:49.803 --> 07:50.871
We gave him
the laxatives,

07:50.904 --> 07:52.405
and right away,
he tried to leave.

07:52.439 --> 07:53.741
Ended up passing out
and vomiting.

07:53.774 --> 07:55.142
I'm fine.
I can take care
of this at home.

07:55.175 --> 07:56.644
We need to
get him to Radiology.

07:56.677 --> 07:58.311
We need an
abdominal CT stat.

07:58.345 --> 08:00.948
No. You can't keep me...
Can't keep me against my will.

08:00.981 --> 08:02.449
Wherever you need to be,
it can wait.

08:02.482 --> 08:03.617
You need help now.

08:03.651 --> 08:05.152
What are you transporting?

08:05.185 --> 08:07.454
Painful constipation,
nervous agitation,

08:07.487 --> 08:09.156
refusing scans...

08:09.189 --> 08:10.658
You're obviously
packing drugs.

08:10.691 --> 08:13.293
The balloons have either
created a complete obstruction

08:13.326 --> 08:15.428
or one of them burst.

08:15.462 --> 08:17.064
Please,
I just want to go home.

08:17.931 --> 08:20.467
Luca, we're doctors,
not cops.

08:20.500 --> 08:22.335
He definitely sounds
like a cop.

08:23.537 --> 08:25.639
We won't
call the police,
I promise.

08:25.673 --> 08:27.941
Whatever is wrong,
let us help you.

08:27.975 --> 08:29.843
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

08:30.611 --> 08:32.680
(MRI MACHINE WHIRRING)

08:34.181 --> 08:35.916
How's Carly?

08:35.949 --> 08:37.651
She wasn't upset
about you ghosting her

08:37.685 --> 08:38.819
while you were with Lea
in Wyoming?

08:38.852 --> 08:41.221
She said it was hurtful.

08:42.089 --> 08:43.456
You got off easy.

08:43.490 --> 08:45.859
Is this your weird way
of breaking up with Carly
to get with Lea?

08:45.893 --> 08:47.527
I don't want to
break up with Carly.

08:47.561 --> 08:49.196
But you do
want to get with Lea.

08:49.229 --> 08:50.530
I didn't say that.

08:50.564 --> 08:51.799
Not out loud.

08:53.533 --> 08:55.502
And you're making
a big mistake.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.671
Carly's smart.
Pretty.

08:57.705 --> 08:59.840
And the fact that
she's willing to dea
l with all your stuff

08:59.873 --> 09:01.609
means you should be thanking
whatever God you pray to

09:01.642 --> 09:02.810
that you ever met her.

09:03.644 --> 09:07.347
While Lea is...
Well, a flake.

09:07.380 --> 09:09.983
She's not a flake.

09:10.918 --> 09:12.319
She showed up
on your doorstep

09:12.352 --> 09:13.887
without even giving you
a heads-up

09:13.921 --> 09:15.388
that she was coming back
to San Jose.

09:15.422 --> 09:18.391
Then she needed to move out,
but then she moves in.

09:18.425 --> 09:19.593
Not to mention the whole

09:19.627 --> 09:21.361
"Let's get drunk on tequila
and I'll teach you
how to kiss,

09:21.394 --> 09:22.930
"but I just want to
be friends" nonsense.

09:25.232 --> 09:29.102
She's...not a flake.

09:31.605 --> 09:33.774
There is traumatic avulsion
of the ligaments.

09:34.942 --> 09:36.677
She's going to
need surgery.

09:42.382 --> 09:45.385
We hammer a long rod
through the medullary canal

09:45.418 --> 09:47.020
to hold the two ends
of the break together.

09:47.054 --> 09:48.889
It's a broken leg.

09:48.922 --> 09:52.559
Can't you just
put a cast on it
or something?

09:52.592 --> 09:54.594
Obviously, you'll be asleep.
You won't feel anything.

09:56.964 --> 09:58.198
I lied.

09:59.032 --> 10:01.468
About the Vicodin
making me sick.

10:01.501 --> 10:03.637
(SIGHS)

10:03.671 --> 10:05.338
My husband doesn't know.

10:06.674 --> 10:08.341
I'm an opioid addict.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.879
I've been clean
for 10 years,

10:11.912 --> 10:13.781
but one dose could
send me right back.

10:13.814 --> 10:16.416
Do whatever
you need to do
to fix my leg,

10:16.449 --> 10:18.919
but you can't
use any narcotics.

10:18.952 --> 10:21.689
**

10:28.095 --> 10:29.797
Not even an epidural?

10:29.830 --> 10:31.732
Strongest thing she'll let us
give her is Tylenol.

10:31.765 --> 10:34.201
Ketamine?
What about Ketamine?

10:34.234 --> 10:37.604
It's non-narcotic
and can create
a dissociative effect.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.539
It's mind altering
and potentially addictive.

10:41.775 --> 10:43.811
Hypnosis has been shown
to be effective.

10:43.844 --> 10:46.613
Only when used
in conjunction
with narcotics.

10:46.646 --> 10:48.982
Studies say playing
the patient's favorite music

10:49.016 --> 10:51.218
can help manage pain
in certain surgeries.

10:51.251 --> 10:53.921
DR. REZNICK: Yeah,
we hammer a nine-inch
rod through her tibia,

10:53.954 --> 10:55.355
but she's okay
because she's listening

10:55.388 --> 10:56.824
to the soundtrack
from Hamilton.

10:56.857 --> 11:00.360
I said
"certain surgeries."

11:00.393 --> 11:01.795
Okay.
That's the answer.

11:02.495 --> 11:03.530
Music?

11:03.563 --> 11:05.432
A different surgery.

11:05.465 --> 11:07.367
Some other way of
putting her leg back together.

11:09.536 --> 11:10.738
An external fixation.

11:13.106 --> 11:15.542
We put two pins through
the proximal tibia.

11:15.575 --> 11:18.078
Another two in the
distal end of the bone
beyond the fractures.

11:18.111 --> 11:19.847
Healing will take
much longer,

11:19.880 --> 11:21.081
and there's
an increased risk

11:21.114 --> 11:23.083
of infection
and permanent
deformity and...

11:23.116 --> 11:26.119
And small pins are much less
painful than a huge nail.

11:28.321 --> 11:29.489
I'll get her prepped.

11:31.124 --> 11:33.626
(MRI MACHINE WHIRS)

11:33.660 --> 11:35.328
(MACHINE PULSING)

11:41.501 --> 11:42.870
I got laid off.

11:44.337 --> 11:47.174
I needed money,
and this was just
a one-time thing.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.777
But it was a mistake.
It was a stupid mistake.

11:52.612 --> 11:54.214
This works best
if you don't talk.

11:59.719 --> 12:03.156
Our plan is to attach
a metal frame with
pins into your leg.

12:03.190 --> 12:05.125
It'll stabilize
the fractures,

12:05.158 --> 12:07.694
and we can do it without
narcotic anesthesia.

12:07.727 --> 12:11.064
I know she's worried
about an allergic
reaction,

12:11.098 --> 12:13.166
but aren't there any other
drugs you can use?

12:13.200 --> 12:15.002
**

12:18.605 --> 12:20.240
Given your wife's
medical history,

12:20.273 --> 12:21.441
this is the best
strategy.

12:23.176 --> 12:25.345
Don't worry, sweetie.

12:25.378 --> 12:27.414
Remember... I'm strong
like Wonder Woman.

12:27.447 --> 12:29.649
(CHUCKLES)

12:33.887 --> 12:35.422
There's over
50 latex balloons

12:35.455 --> 12:37.090
lodged near
the ileocecal junction.

12:37.124 --> 12:38.758
They'll need to be
surgically removed.

12:38.792 --> 12:40.727
And we need to alert
San Jose Vice/Narcotics.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.029
No.

12:42.062 --> 12:43.430
The only reason
he agreed to treatment

12:43.463 --> 12:44.865
is because we promised
we wouldn't do that.

12:44.898 --> 12:46.900
I didn't promise that.
Neither did Dr. Melendez.

12:46.934 --> 12:48.201
We don't call
the police

12:48.235 --> 12:50.237
on overdose victims
or addicts.

12:50.270 --> 12:51.771
He's got
probably two kilos

12:51.805 --> 12:53.773
of what I'm sure
is heroin in his gut.

12:53.807 --> 12:55.608
He's not an addict.
He's a dealer.

12:57.811 --> 12:59.246
I know you feel
for this guy.

12:59.279 --> 13:01.114
But hospital policy
is clear.

13:01.148 --> 13:02.816
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS,
DOORS OPEN)

13:07.287 --> 13:09.222
(SIGHS)

13:09.256 --> 13:11.724
DR. REZNICK: Take a few more
of those deep breaths for us.

13:11.758 --> 13:13.726
(BREATHING HEAVILY)
DR. ANDREWS: Just
two more to go.

13:13.760 --> 13:15.395
(CLASSICAL MUSIC
PLAYING ON STEREO)

13:15.428 --> 13:18.131
Kerry, we need you
to somehow
keep your leg still.

13:18.165 --> 13:19.399
(WHIMPERS)

13:19.432 --> 13:20.733
(DRILL WHIRS)

13:20.767 --> 13:22.903
(MONITOR ALARM BEEPING)

13:22.936 --> 13:24.972
B.P. is 190/110.
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

13:25.005 --> 13:26.606
Push I.V. beta blockers.

13:26.639 --> 13:27.807
Wait, no!
No, they're not narcotics.

13:27.841 --> 13:29.642
We just need to
give you something
to reduce the pressure.

13:29.676 --> 13:31.378
(WHIMPERS)

13:31.411 --> 13:33.680
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

13:33.713 --> 13:34.915
(ALARM STOPS)

13:34.948 --> 13:36.850
Back to 150/80.

13:36.884 --> 13:39.152
Kerry,
how are we doing?
Better.

13:39.186 --> 13:42.455
We'll get this last one in,
and you'll be good to go.

13:42.489 --> 13:45.658
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

13:46.326 --> 13:48.295
No. You promised me.

13:48.328 --> 13:51.231
Yeah. You value honesty
and morality over all else.

13:51.264 --> 13:53.934
If you leave
this hospital now,
you will die.

13:53.967 --> 13:55.802
I'll take my chances.

13:55.835 --> 13:58.838
You know what'll happen
when one those
balloons bursts?

13:58.872 --> 14:01.708
You'll start
feeling weak,
get cold.

14:01.741 --> 14:04.044
Soon you'll have secretions
filling your lungs and airway.

14:04.077 --> 14:07.280
You'll try to scream for help,
but nothing will come out.

14:07.314 --> 14:09.316
**

14:13.620 --> 14:15.222
Can you get
the release paperwork?

14:19.292 --> 14:20.627
I'll be back
in a few minutes.

14:21.828 --> 14:24.864
Luca, I understand
where you're coming from.

14:24.898 --> 14:26.066
You're a doctor.

14:26.099 --> 14:28.335
Last job I had,
I was a busboy.

14:28.368 --> 14:29.769
(GROANS)

14:32.672 --> 14:34.174
(INHALES SHAKILY)

14:36.376 --> 14:37.911
I grew up in a trailer.

14:37.945 --> 14:39.146
A bunch of 'em,
actually.

14:39.179 --> 14:41.748
My mother wasn't the type
to save for a rainy day.

14:42.950 --> 14:44.317
But we never gave up.

14:45.385 --> 14:47.720
Even when you think
you're alone, you're not.

14:47.754 --> 14:49.822
I want to help you.

14:49.856 --> 14:52.092
You just have to give me
a little more time.

14:53.226 --> 14:54.227
One hour.

14:55.195 --> 14:57.330
If I can't figure out
how to treat you

14:57.364 --> 14:59.432
and keep you out of jail,
you can walk out the door.

15:03.736 --> 15:04.938
One hour.

15:04.972 --> 15:06.206
And then I'm gone.

15:06.239 --> 15:08.708
**

15:14.747 --> 15:17.250
You'll have some discomfort
for the next few weeks,

15:17.284 --> 15:20.553
but all you need
right now is rest,
and you should be able...

15:20.587 --> 15:21.688
Mommy!
Hey.

15:21.721 --> 15:23.957
Oh, my gosh,
that's so cool.

15:23.991 --> 15:25.592
(BOYD CHUCKLES)

15:25.625 --> 15:28.295
Everyone says their
spouse is the strongest
person they know.

15:30.130 --> 15:31.564
But I have
actual proof now.

15:32.865 --> 15:34.667
Told you.

15:34.701 --> 15:35.735
Wonder Woman.

15:37.804 --> 15:38.871
This is absurd.

15:38.905 --> 15:40.740
If this was a tumor,
we'd take it out
and toss it.

15:40.773 --> 15:42.275
This time,
it just happens
to be drugs.

15:42.309 --> 15:45.078
Yeah, because cancer
is not a felony.

15:45.112 --> 15:47.047
You can't just toss out
the drugs with
the medical waste.

15:47.080 --> 15:50.450
He's not a gangster
or a hardened criminal.

15:50.483 --> 15:53.120
He's just...
He's just a scared guy
trying to survive.

15:53.153 --> 15:54.954
DR. PARK: You're
assuming anything
he's told you is true.

15:54.988 --> 15:56.223
And even if it is,

15:56.256 --> 15:58.425
not everyone
who needs money
becomes a drug mule.

15:58.458 --> 15:59.726
You can't imagine
what it's like

15:59.759 --> 16:01.394
to grow up
in that kind of poverty.

16:01.428 --> 16:03.763
Shouldn't you be judging
this guy the harshest?

16:03.796 --> 16:05.732
You made it out just fine
without breaking the law.

16:07.934 --> 16:09.602
That's not exactly true.

16:12.139 --> 16:13.973
My mother used to
go on these trips.

16:14.007 --> 16:16.743
I would come home
from school,
and she'd be gone.

16:16.776 --> 16:19.346
Sometimes hours,
sometimes days.

16:19.379 --> 16:21.181
I didn't have any money.

16:21.214 --> 16:24.251
So when I needed supplies
and food from the store,

16:24.284 --> 16:27.354
I would sneak them away
in a backpack.

16:27.387 --> 16:29.122
One day,
the bag broke

16:29.156 --> 16:32.725
and all of the soup
and oatmeal that I had stolen

16:32.759 --> 16:35.228
fell out right in front of
a security guard.

16:36.596 --> 16:39.332
And she looked at me,

16:39.366 --> 16:41.901
at my face,
at my clothes,

16:41.934 --> 16:43.170
and then she helped me
pick them up

16:43.203 --> 16:45.772
and let me go
with a warning.

16:45.805 --> 16:47.140
If she hadn't
given me a break,

16:47.174 --> 16:49.942
I wouldn't be
standing here,
as a doctor,

16:49.976 --> 16:52.179
discussing this
with you.

16:52.212 --> 16:54.481
**

16:56.249 --> 16:58.485
Maybe there's a way
to save Luca

16:58.518 --> 17:00.987
without ruining his life
or breaking policy.

17:09.962 --> 17:11.831
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

17:16.836 --> 17:18.805
Shaun.

17:18.838 --> 17:20.673
You need the elevator.
Use the elevator.

17:33.986 --> 17:35.822
(ELEVATOR WHIRRING)

17:39.092 --> 17:41.528
What am I doing wrong?

17:41.561 --> 17:44.664
I never know
where I stand
with you.

17:44.697 --> 17:46.699
One minute,
we're sharing

17:46.733 --> 17:48.501
deep, personal fears
with each other,

17:48.535 --> 17:49.869
and the next,
you're running away

17:49.902 --> 17:51.604
because you can't
stand to touch me.

17:55.408 --> 17:57.076
Be honest...

17:57.110 --> 17:59.246
Is there anything
going on with Lea

17:59.279 --> 18:00.613
that you're not
telling me?

18:05.652 --> 18:06.719
Say something, Shaun.

18:06.753 --> 18:08.255
It's different.

18:08.288 --> 18:10.490
**

18:13.059 --> 18:17.964
I...like you, Carly.

18:19.799 --> 18:22.769
When I'm around you,

18:22.802 --> 18:26.373
I want to be
impressive to you.

18:26.406 --> 18:30.443
I don't feel like
I have to impress
Lea like I do you.

18:32.579 --> 18:34.847
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS,
DOORS OPEN)

18:34.881 --> 18:36.983
**

18:39.652 --> 18:41.621
(DOORS CLOSE)

18:43.223 --> 18:44.691
CLAIRE:
We will have to keep

18:44.724 --> 18:48.295
whatever medical waste
we collect during your surgery
in the lab for testing.

18:48.328 --> 18:50.129
But we will discharge you

18:50.163 --> 18:51.998
before the pathology report
comes back.

18:53.132 --> 18:55.668
At which point
we'll be obligated
to alert the police.

18:56.669 --> 18:58.271
How do I know you're not
gonna call the cops

18:58.305 --> 18:59.406
right after
you put me to sleep?

18:59.439 --> 19:02.475
You'd be a moron
not to trust Dr. Browne
at this point.

19:02.509 --> 19:04.444
She's gone way
beyond the call
to save your ass.

19:06.779 --> 19:07.814
Okay.

19:07.847 --> 19:09.249
Say thank you.

19:12.352 --> 19:13.353
Thank you.

19:16.356 --> 19:18.991
**

19:44.551 --> 19:46.953
Dr. Murphy.

19:46.986 --> 19:48.488
How about
you head home
for the night?

19:48.521 --> 19:50.657
We still need to
monitor Kerry.

19:50.690 --> 19:53.092
And it's easier for me
to avoid Carly here

19:53.125 --> 19:55.094
than it is for me to
avoid Lea at home.

19:55.127 --> 19:57.964
Okay,
I'm only gonna respond
to the first objection.

19:57.997 --> 19:59.165
You've had a long week,

19:59.198 --> 20:00.367
and it's important
you get some rest.

20:00.400 --> 20:01.768
Morgan will take point.

20:04.203 --> 20:08.207
How did you know
your wife was
the right woman for you?

20:08.241 --> 20:09.409
Personal advice?

20:11.043 --> 20:13.045
I thought that was
Dr. Glassman's domain.

20:14.180 --> 20:17.284
Dr. Glassman
is divorced.

20:17.317 --> 20:19.218
He seems happy with
his marriage now,

20:19.252 --> 20:21.721
but I have no way
of knowing for sure.

20:21.754 --> 20:22.989
You're better than him.

20:24.190 --> 20:25.325
For this.

20:27.026 --> 20:29.429
**

20:31.931 --> 20:34.867
I knew I wanted to
be with Isabel
the first time we spoke.

20:34.901 --> 20:36.503
Freshman-year
biology class.

20:36.536 --> 20:39.572
And I have not wavered
in that resolve
in the 27 years since.

20:41.741 --> 20:43.042
But...

20:43.075 --> 20:44.711
How did you know?

20:46.946 --> 20:50.683
It was a feeling I had
in the pit of my stomach

20:50.717 --> 20:52.151
every time
I was around her.

20:52.184 --> 20:53.420
I felt...

20:53.453 --> 20:54.554
Nervous?

20:54.587 --> 20:55.788
Excited.

20:57.390 --> 20:59.359
It's a cliche,

20:59.392 --> 21:01.894
but my heart sped up
every time I saw her.

21:01.928 --> 21:03.530
Still does.

21:03.563 --> 21:06.032
Not quite
in the same way,
but...

21:06.065 --> 21:08.568
**

21:11.471 --> 21:13.640
Now, if you don't mind,
I need to get home
to that woman.

21:27.587 --> 21:29.288
Hey, you.

21:29.322 --> 21:30.923
How was
the first day back?

21:30.957 --> 21:31.958
Confusing.

21:32.825 --> 21:35.094
Problem with a patient
or Carly?

21:43.436 --> 21:45.538
If you don't want to
talk about it,
we can just hang.

21:45.572 --> 21:47.907
Let's just hang.

21:47.940 --> 21:50.042
Copy that.
Commencing a hang.

21:53.813 --> 21:56.883
**

22:16.703 --> 22:19.839
Um, Sh... Shaun?

22:19.872 --> 22:21.073
Hm.

22:22.375 --> 22:23.443
What's up?

22:23.476 --> 22:25.778
This will just take
a few seconds.

22:25.812 --> 22:28.180
(HEART BEATING)

22:28.214 --> 22:30.517
**

22:32.084 --> 22:33.620
(SIGHS)

22:36.489 --> 22:38.157
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

22:40.660 --> 22:41.694
Hello?

22:41.728 --> 22:42.795
DR. REZNICK:
It didn't work.

22:42.829 --> 22:44.497
Kerry's leg
is swelling up.

22:44.531 --> 22:46.533
I think she has
compartment syndrome.

22:46.566 --> 22:48.067
You need to get back here.

22:48.100 --> 22:49.969
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

22:50.002 --> 22:51.904
**

22:55.908 --> 22:59.546
We'll have to do the surgery
we've been trying to avoid.

22:59.579 --> 23:02.314
We'll first have to make
multiple incisions
to relieve the pressure

23:02.348 --> 23:05.552
and then replace
the external frame
with an internal nail.

23:05.585 --> 23:07.920
If we don't act soon,

23:07.954 --> 23:09.656
you could be facing
an amputation.

23:11.424 --> 23:12.425
Okay.

23:13.493 --> 23:14.527
You'll need to be
sedated.

23:14.561 --> 23:17.096
No.
Look, I can take it.

23:17.129 --> 23:19.398
Kerry, you had
a blood-pressure spike

23:19.432 --> 23:20.933
during the fixation
procedure.

23:20.967 --> 23:22.301
Without anesthesia,

23:22.334 --> 23:23.936
you could have
a hypertensive crisis,

23:23.970 --> 23:26.338
a risk of stroke,
or heart attack.

23:27.607 --> 23:29.776
Post-op,
we can help you
manage the dosing.

23:29.809 --> 23:32.545
And if you relapse,
we have counselors that...

23:32.579 --> 23:33.713
No.

23:37.617 --> 23:41.588
I remember waking up
all those mornings
cold and alone,

23:41.621 --> 23:44.957
wondering if I could ever
be happy again,

23:44.991 --> 23:47.059
if I deserved
to be happy.

23:48.961 --> 23:54.066
Any amount of pain
is better than losing
everything again.

23:54.100 --> 23:55.935
My husband,
my daughter...

23:57.269 --> 24:00.573
How long can you
keep secrets from
the people you love

24:00.607 --> 24:02.742
before they stop being
the people you love?

24:05.545 --> 24:07.413
Every relationship
has secrets.

24:08.748 --> 24:11.117
This, it doesn't
have to be
one of them.

24:11.150 --> 24:13.553
Drug addiction
is a disease.

24:13.586 --> 24:15.555
You have nothing
to be ashamed of.

24:16.656 --> 24:18.958
It happens because of
the choices you make.

24:20.960 --> 24:23.930
When you have lost
everything,

24:23.963 --> 24:26.966
but you still manage
to find someone

24:26.999 --> 24:29.736
who makes you want to get up
and live another day,

24:29.769 --> 24:32.839
you do whatever you can
to hold on to them,

24:34.273 --> 24:36.142
even if it means

24:36.175 --> 24:39.746
burying a piece of yourself
in the process.

24:39.779 --> 24:41.347
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

24:45.151 --> 24:47.386
If we can't convince her
to change her mind,

24:48.621 --> 24:49.922
maybe her husband can.

24:49.956 --> 24:51.991
Impracticality isn't cause

24:52.024 --> 24:54.126
for breaking doctor-patient
confidentiality.

24:54.160 --> 24:55.828
This isn't impractical.

24:55.862 --> 24:57.997
It's irrational
and barbaric.

25:00.232 --> 25:03.202
We're not permitted to reveal
any secrets to the husband.

25:04.604 --> 25:07.540
But we can tell him that.

25:10.710 --> 25:12.812
(MONITOR BEEPING)

25:16.949 --> 25:18.484
DR. MELENDEZ: Last one.

25:21.988 --> 25:23.489
(SIGHS)

25:23.522 --> 25:24.591
What's wrong?

25:24.624 --> 25:26.092
It's too adherent
to the intestinal wall.

25:27.093 --> 25:29.328
Could use Potts Scissors
to dissect it free.

25:32.198 --> 25:33.966
Let's give it a try.
Nurse?

25:34.000 --> 25:35.234
**

25:37.203 --> 25:39.438
Your idea.
Only fair you do the honors.

25:52.652 --> 25:54.353
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

25:58.057 --> 25:59.458
DR. MELENDEZ: Check it
for perforations.

26:02.294 --> 26:03.295
DR. PARK: It's intact.

26:04.130 --> 26:05.898
DR. MELENDEZ:
Vitals are stable.

26:05.932 --> 26:07.667
Take the specimen
container to the lab.

26:07.700 --> 26:09.101
Dr. Browne,
you're leading closure.

26:09.135 --> 26:11.537
**

26:18.544 --> 26:19.979
There's been
some complications.

26:20.012 --> 26:22.214
We need to perform
an additional surgery.

26:22.248 --> 26:23.282
What do you need to do?

26:23.315 --> 26:24.717
I can't tell you.

26:26.919 --> 26:28.855
I'm unable to go
into further detail.

26:28.888 --> 26:30.723
It would violate
your wife's confidentiality.

26:30.757 --> 26:32.124
Confidentiality?

26:33.125 --> 26:35.527
Haven't you been
telling me everything?

26:35.561 --> 26:38.497
Again, I'm unable to
go into further detail.

26:40.332 --> 26:42.034
(SIGHS)

26:42.568 --> 26:44.170
Hey.
Hey.

26:44.203 --> 26:45.271
What's going on?

26:45.304 --> 26:47.073
Why can't the doctors
talk to me?

26:47.106 --> 26:48.574
(SIGHS)

26:48.607 --> 26:51.410
Kerry, obviously,
there's something going on
you don't want me to know.

26:51.443 --> 26:52.578
Are you dying?

26:52.611 --> 26:56.182
No. No. It's...

26:56.215 --> 26:58.084
(EXHALES SHARPLY)
It's nothing like that.

26:59.051 --> 27:00.286
(STOOL RATTLES)

27:00.319 --> 27:03.422
Hey. Then what?

27:04.924 --> 27:07.393
Whatever it is,
I want to be able to help.

27:07.426 --> 27:08.527
Please.

27:13.933 --> 27:15.768
I'm an opioid addict.

27:15.802 --> 27:17.937
I've been clean
for a decade, but...

27:21.140 --> 27:24.076
That's why I never
take painkillers.

27:24.110 --> 27:26.278
And that's why I can't
let them use anesthesia.

27:28.014 --> 27:29.515
Why didn't you
ever tell me?

27:32.551 --> 27:34.987
You don't know
the kind of person
that I was.

27:36.689 --> 27:38.324
Who the drugs
turned me into.

27:41.160 --> 27:42.695
I tried quitting
so many times,

27:42.729 --> 27:44.496
but it never stuck.

27:44.530 --> 27:46.799
Until you.

27:46.833 --> 27:49.335
Meeting you saved me.

27:50.703 --> 27:51.838
But...

27:54.173 --> 27:56.809
...if I relapse,
I know I'll drive you away.

27:56.843 --> 27:58.644
Hey, hey.

28:00.579 --> 28:02.749
How could you ever think
I'll stop loving you?

28:04.751 --> 28:07.720
The woman who knows the lyrics
to every Boyz II Men song?

28:07.754 --> 28:08.921
(CHUCKLES)

28:08.955 --> 28:10.189
The woman who rushes home

28:10.222 --> 28:12.358
to watch those stupid
home-makeover shows live.

28:12.391 --> 28:13.525
(SIGHS)

28:16.228 --> 28:17.797
The woman I'm raising
our daughter with.

28:17.830 --> 28:20.032
The woman who will
steal from you,

28:20.066 --> 28:22.668
the woman
who will lie to you,

28:22.701 --> 28:24.336
who will hurt you...
No.

28:24.370 --> 28:26.472
...the woman you won't
be able to trust.

28:26.505 --> 28:27.506
No.

28:31.177 --> 28:33.645
Just do what
the doctors tell you.

28:33.679 --> 28:35.447
Take the meds.

28:36.448 --> 28:38.550
I will be there
for you.

28:38.584 --> 28:40.686
No matter what happens.

28:40.719 --> 28:43.089
**

28:48.227 --> 28:49.695
I love you.

28:51.463 --> 28:53.032
And I know
you mean that.

28:53.065 --> 28:55.401
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

28:55.434 --> 28:57.569
But I'm not as strong
as you think I am.

28:57.603 --> 28:59.271
Baby.
I just can't.

29:00.206 --> 29:01.573
I'm so sorry.

29:01.607 --> 29:03.675
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

29:03.709 --> 29:06.879
**

29:11.951 --> 29:14.153
We'll start prepping you
for surgery.

29:14.186 --> 29:15.955
**

29:17.523 --> 29:19.191
(SIGHS)

29:21.994 --> 29:23.662
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

29:29.735 --> 29:31.871
I like your laugh.
I like your smile.

29:31.904 --> 29:33.739
I don't usually
look at eyes,

29:33.772 --> 29:35.407
but I think
yours are pretty.

29:35.441 --> 29:36.742
I like your breasts.

29:38.110 --> 29:40.246
You can keep going
if you want to.

29:40.279 --> 29:42.514
I like spending time
with you.

29:42.548 --> 29:44.383
I like
that you are kind.

29:44.416 --> 29:46.052
I like
that you are patient.

29:46.085 --> 29:47.854
I like that
you're my girlfriend.

29:49.155 --> 29:50.722
Are you going to
break up with me?

29:50.756 --> 29:53.625
No, I am not planning on
breaking up with you.

29:54.660 --> 29:55.727
We had a fight.

29:55.761 --> 29:57.663
Couples fight.

29:57.696 --> 29:58.697
But...

30:00.266 --> 30:01.600
I'm worried, Shaun.

30:03.870 --> 30:06.906
I'm flattered that
you want to impress me,

30:06.939 --> 30:08.540
but that is not
worth anything

30:08.574 --> 30:10.609
if you feel like
you can't talk to me.

30:10.642 --> 30:12.344
**

30:15.014 --> 30:16.615
Hm. You're right.

30:17.783 --> 30:19.886
I have to tell you.
Everything.

30:21.187 --> 30:23.289
**

30:32.264 --> 30:35.701
I got very upset

30:38.070 --> 30:39.505
in Wyoming.

30:43.342 --> 30:47.713
Lea came in
to comfort me

30:49.548 --> 30:51.450
and we hugged

30:51.483 --> 30:53.319
and laid down
on the bed,

30:54.853 --> 30:56.555
and we fell asleep
hugging.

30:58.390 --> 31:00.092
That's everything
that happened.

31:03.762 --> 31:07.299
We struggled
with lying together
for weeks.

31:07.333 --> 31:09.701
And you...

31:09.735 --> 31:11.637
Did it in one night
with Lea?

31:11.670 --> 31:13.505
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

31:13.539 --> 31:14.540
Yes.

31:15.741 --> 31:19.645
But sh... She's
a close friend,

31:19.678 --> 31:22.148
and she wanted
to be there for me.

31:22.181 --> 31:24.216
Please,
just stop talking.

31:24.250 --> 31:26.085
(SIGHS)

31:26.118 --> 31:29.055
Shaun, I-I just...
I need some space.

31:29.088 --> 31:30.522
I can't be around you
right now.

31:30.556 --> 31:33.125
**

31:40.732 --> 31:42.201
(SIGHS)

31:44.703 --> 31:46.405
Shaun?

31:46.438 --> 31:47.940
I wanted to be honest.
(DOOR CLOSES)

31:47.974 --> 31:49.775
Carly said she wanted me
to talk to her.

31:49.808 --> 31:51.543
Lea said not to tell what
happened. Lea was right.

31:51.577 --> 31:52.878
Uh, take a breath.
Sit down.

31:52.911 --> 31:55.781
I can't.
I have surgery
in a few minutes

31:55.814 --> 31:58.650
and I can't focus and...

31:58.684 --> 32:02.288
And I feel sick,
and is everyone
going to leave me?

32:02.321 --> 32:04.423
What? What?
What are you
talking about?

32:04.456 --> 32:05.691
My dad didn't want me.

32:06.592 --> 32:11.363
My mom chose him
over me.

32:11.397 --> 32:13.032
Carly now hates me.

32:13.065 --> 32:14.266
Shaun. Shaun.
Lea will get tired
of me.

32:14.300 --> 32:15.734
Shaun.
You'll get sick of me.

32:15.767 --> 32:16.969
I do everything wrong.
What?

32:17.003 --> 32:18.904
Shaun, Shaun,
look at me for a second.
Everyone will go away!

32:18.937 --> 32:20.606
I make people upset!
Hey, hey, Shaun!

32:20.639 --> 32:22.708
Oh, my God, Shaun!
I make them angry!
I make them hate me!

32:22.741 --> 32:24.876
Shaun, look at me, look at me,
look at me right here.

32:24.910 --> 32:26.712
Right here.
Look at me here.

32:26.745 --> 32:28.380
Don't ever say that
about yourself.

32:28.414 --> 32:30.049
Don't ever say that!

32:30.082 --> 32:31.150
You hear me?

32:31.183 --> 32:33.652
(PANTING)

32:34.420 --> 32:35.687
You're gonna
get through this.

32:35.721 --> 32:37.456
You're gonna go to surgery,
and you're gonna
get this done.

32:37.489 --> 32:38.557
How?
How?

32:38.590 --> 32:40.259
Because you're an
extraordinary doctor.

32:40.292 --> 32:41.560
That's how.

32:41.593 --> 32:44.296
And that's what you do.
That's what you do.

32:44.330 --> 32:47.433
(SIGHS)
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

32:47.466 --> 32:49.001
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

32:49.035 --> 32:51.637
I could not be
more proud of you.

32:53.205 --> 32:54.573
You hear that?

32:55.741 --> 32:57.476
And I could never
get sick of you.

32:57.509 --> 32:59.211
(CHUCKLES)

33:00.579 --> 33:02.148
(SIGHS)

33:05.651 --> 33:07.986
You're not getting
rid of me, pal, okay?

33:08.020 --> 33:10.956
(BREATHES SHAKILY)
I'm right here.

33:10.989 --> 33:13.359
(CHUCKLES)
Right... Right here.

33:14.126 --> 33:16.362
Okay? (CHUCKLES)
I got you.

33:20.299 --> 33:21.900
I'm going to be late
to surgery.

33:21.933 --> 33:23.335
Can you let me go now?

33:23.369 --> 33:25.137
Yeah, okay.

33:26.705 --> 33:27.839
Okay.

33:27.873 --> 33:29.308
Okay.

33:33.979 --> 33:35.347
(MONITOR BEEPING)

33:39.251 --> 33:40.819
SHAUN:
Numbing cream applied.

33:46.024 --> 33:47.359
Are you ready?

33:47.393 --> 33:49.027
(SIGHS)

33:53.365 --> 33:56.668
(CLAUDE DEBUSSY'S
CLAIR DE LUNE
PLAYS ON STEREO)

33:56.702 --> 33:59.071
**

34:01.373 --> 34:04.976
(GRUNTS LOUDLY, GROANS)

34:06.044 --> 34:08.714
We were able to remove
all the balloons.

34:08.747 --> 34:11.217
So you should
be out of here
in 24 hours.

34:11.983 --> 34:14.686
It'll likely take
another 48 hours

34:14.720 --> 34:16.122
to get the contents
tested.

34:16.822 --> 34:18.424
The lab's very busy.

34:21.660 --> 34:23.362
I know I've been
a pain in the ass.

34:25.197 --> 34:27.199
I've just gotten
used to people
screwing me over.

34:28.467 --> 34:30.836
You're the first person
that's made me feel,

34:32.204 --> 34:33.872
I don't know, seen.

34:35.741 --> 34:38.877
Maybe one day, I'll find a way
to pay it forward, right?

34:41.613 --> 34:43.615
(CHUCKLES)

34:43.649 --> 34:45.151
(DRILL WHIRRING)

34:45.184 --> 34:47.186
(CLAIR DE LUNE CONTINUES
PLAYING ON STEREO)

34:48.754 --> 34:50.356
DR. ANDREWS: Reamer's in
the intramedullary canal.

34:50.389 --> 34:52.191
DR. REZNICK:
This will make space
for inserting the nail.

34:52.224 --> 34:53.259
(WHIMPERS LOUDLY)

34:53.292 --> 34:54.560
You're doing great,
Kerry.

34:54.593 --> 34:55.994
Inserting into canal.

34:56.027 --> 34:57.763
DR. REZNICK:
Here comes the nail.
You ready?

34:57.796 --> 34:59.598
(EXHALES SHAKILY)

34:59.631 --> 35:01.267
(GROANING, CRYING)

35:01.300 --> 35:02.868
(MONITOR ALARM BEEPING)

35:02.901 --> 35:04.936
B.P.'s spiking.
Push beta blockers.

35:07.973 --> 35:10.609
(SCREAMING)

35:10.642 --> 35:12.278
Hang in there.

35:12.311 --> 35:14.580
SHAUN: 220/170.

35:14.613 --> 35:16.315
She's having
a tachyarrhythmia.

35:16.348 --> 35:17.849
Screw it.
We have to push
the fentanyl.

35:17.883 --> 35:19.851
(ADHESIVE RIPS)
(GRUNTS)

35:19.885 --> 35:22.120
(ALARM CONTINUES)

35:22.154 --> 35:23.222
Nurse,
help Dr. Murphy.

35:23.255 --> 35:26.325
No. It's helping
distract her.

35:26.358 --> 35:27.559
You sure, Dr. Murphy?

35:27.593 --> 35:29.228
Yes. Please hurry.

35:30.629 --> 35:33.064
(HAMMER TAPPING)

35:33.098 --> 35:34.966
(MUSIC CONTINUES ON STEREO)

35:35.000 --> 35:37.236
(INHALES SHARPLY)

35:40.339 --> 35:43.809
It was a good day.
(CHUCKLES)

35:43.842 --> 35:46.578
It must be very gratifying,
saving lives.

35:46.612 --> 35:49.080
Yeah, I think I might've
done a little more
than that today.

35:49.114 --> 35:52.518
I... I think
I might have
changed one.

35:52.551 --> 35:54.520
(CHUCKLES)

35:55.821 --> 35:57.423
Last time we met,

35:57.456 --> 36:00.058
you mentioned
that your mother

36:00.091 --> 36:02.828
would frequently berate you
when you were young.

36:04.996 --> 36:07.599
What kind of things
would she say?

36:07.633 --> 36:09.368
(SCOFFS LIGHTLY)

36:09.401 --> 36:11.036
Do we have to
get into that
right now?

36:12.204 --> 36:14.773
Can't I just
have a good day?

36:14.806 --> 36:16.308
(CHUCKLES)

36:16.342 --> 36:18.277
You know,
enjoy feeling okay
for once?

36:18.310 --> 36:22.648
Claire, I believe
you've fallen into
destructive patterns

36:22.681 --> 36:27.553
precisely to avoid
confronting your feelings
about your mother,

36:27.586 --> 36:29.721
her death.

36:29.755 --> 36:31.957
Feelings that need
to be confronted

36:31.990 --> 36:33.725
if you hope
to get better.

36:35.026 --> 36:36.828
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

36:36.862 --> 36:37.863
Uh...

36:41.066 --> 36:42.501
(INHALES SHARPLY)

36:45.237 --> 36:46.305
(P.A. SYSTEM BEEPS)

36:46.338 --> 36:48.006
WOMAN ON P.A.:
Cardiac care nurse to E.R.

36:48.039 --> 36:49.107
Cardiac care nurse to E.R.

36:49.140 --> 36:50.976
(DOOR OPENS)

36:51.009 --> 36:53.345
They're reviewing
the security video.

36:53.379 --> 36:56.582
Someone faked a seizure,
staff responded,

36:56.615 --> 36:58.617
and another person broke into
the storage locker.

37:00.786 --> 37:02.187
Do you think Luca...

37:02.220 --> 37:03.855
The only thing missing
was his specimen.

37:04.756 --> 37:05.857
Is someone
questioning him?

37:09.595 --> 37:10.662
Luca's gone.

37:10.696 --> 37:14.366
(WILDES' CIRCLES PLAYS)

37:14.400 --> 37:15.434
What will the police do?

37:15.467 --> 37:16.568
Nothing.

37:16.602 --> 37:18.304
All we have is a fake name
and the knowledge

37:18.337 --> 37:20.739
that someone stole
some balloons
with unknown content.

37:23.174 --> 37:25.744
* If I weigh in

37:27.178 --> 37:30.849
* You'll give me
a reason to say it

37:30.882 --> 37:32.518
She definitely is
a Wonder Woman.

37:35.186 --> 37:36.888
You were right
the first time.

37:37.923 --> 37:39.425
She's totally irrational.

37:39.458 --> 37:40.992
Needlessly endangered
her life.

37:43.094 --> 37:45.163
But I understand why.

37:45.196 --> 37:48.767
* To these motions

37:48.800 --> 37:54.072
* Scattered with our words
never spoken

37:56.107 --> 38:01.713
* Ooh-ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh

38:01.747 --> 38:04.750
* Mm-mm-mm

38:04.783 --> 38:09.888
* All the circles
that we move in

38:09.921 --> 38:12.223
My mother used to say
I'd end up like her...

38:14.125 --> 38:16.294
Putting my faith
in the wrong people,

38:16.328 --> 38:17.796
getting taken
advantage of.

38:20.499 --> 38:23.602
That no one would ever
truly love me except her.

38:28.106 --> 38:29.675
There are worse qualities
in this world

38:29.708 --> 38:31.443
than trying to see
the best in people.

38:36.114 --> 38:37.516
If you're a good person,

38:39.685 --> 38:42.754
every now and again,
you're gonna feel
like an idiot.

38:42.788 --> 38:44.255
Today you were wrong.

38:46.892 --> 38:49.060
And I am still grateful
that I work with you.

38:51.162 --> 38:53.131
* Dreadful silence

38:53.164 --> 38:54.165
Thank you.

38:55.133 --> 38:59.905
* Waiting for
the moment to break it

39:02.173 --> 39:06.177
* I've been slipping

39:06.211 --> 39:12.150
* But I think that
I'm gonna make it

39:13.619 --> 39:15.721
Have you had
enough space yet?

39:17.188 --> 39:20.792
* I lost you in the smoke

39:20.826 --> 39:23.895
**

39:23.929 --> 39:27.899
* And I've tried patience

39:27.933 --> 39:31.903
* But we've just overgrown

39:31.937 --> 39:34.105
Shaun, do you remember
the first time we met?

39:35.541 --> 39:39.377
* Ooh-ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh

39:39.411 --> 39:41.913
I was checking
on a biopsy

39:41.947 --> 39:45.083
to see if the tumor margins
were in the artery walls.

39:45.116 --> 39:47.018
Yeah.

39:47.052 --> 39:49.821
And you said
if I didn't do it
right then,

39:49.855 --> 39:51.723
you would toss a rock
through my window.

39:53.024 --> 39:54.259
Yes.

39:55.494 --> 39:58.196
I thought it was cute
how much you cared.

39:59.798 --> 40:02.601
And when you started
working in Path,
I realized,

40:04.102 --> 40:07.773
"This guy may be
the most genuine person
I have ever known."

40:12.511 --> 40:13.912
You told me the truth.

40:15.614 --> 40:16.982
That is a good thing.

40:19.284 --> 40:20.752
That's why I like you.

40:23.755 --> 40:25.624
That's why I don't want
to lose what we have.

40:27.926 --> 40:29.961
* Ooh-ooh-ooh

40:29.995 --> 40:31.563
You hurt me.

40:31.597 --> 40:35.200
* Ooh-ooh

40:35.233 --> 40:38.570
And I worry
something like that
could happen again.

40:39.437 --> 40:42.073
* That we move in

40:42.107 --> 40:44.710
* Remind me of the love...

40:44.743 --> 40:47.479
I want to be with you,
Shaun.

40:48.980 --> 40:50.716
But I don't know
how this works

40:50.749 --> 40:53.151
if you're still
living with Lea.

40:53.184 --> 40:56.454
* Then why
are we still suffering?

40:56.488 --> 40:57.723
You...

41:00.025 --> 41:02.994
Want me
not to live with Lea?

41:03.995 --> 41:05.497
* Ooh-ooh-ooh

41:07.198 --> 41:08.967
I know that's
a lot to ask.

41:12.003 --> 41:13.639
And if it's too much...

41:16.675 --> 41:18.143
I understand.

41:18.176 --> 41:21.146
* I thought love was true

41:21.179 --> 41:22.748
* But loneliness won, too

41:22.781 --> 41:25.183
You don't have to answer
right away.

41:25.216 --> 41:27.719
* Love's been runnin' out

41:27.753 --> 41:29.621
Take some time.

41:29.655 --> 41:35.360
* Maybe I'll find solitude
without you

41:37.162 --> 41:42.601
* All the circles
that we move in

41:42.634 --> 41:48.273
* Remind me of the love
we've wasted

41:48.306 --> 41:53.378
* If we're searching
for the same thing

41:53.411 --> 41:54.412
Okay.

41:57.415 --> 41:58.650
Okay?

41:59.618 --> 42:03.388
I want to be with you.

42:03.421 --> 42:06.224
* Ooh-ooh-ooh *

42:06.257 --> 42:07.659
I love you, Carly.

42:10.228 --> 42:11.396
(CHUCKLES)

42:12.230 --> 42:14.432
**

42:30.448 --> 42:32.918
**
